The paper discusses Constraint Handling Rules (CHR), which is a programming language used for constraint solving. This falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it is used for solving complex problems. The paper also discusses semantics and analysis, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses systems and extensions, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses applications, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
